blocks: <h3>1 Comment.</h3><p>What exactly is God saving us from? The idea that we even need saving is distinct to certain religions.</p><p>The flaw in Hough's logic is this. If God has multiple options to "save" us why would it involve needlessly crucifying his son?</p><p>Perhaps God is not unconditionally free? The idea sounds good, but doesn't hold up to logic.</p>
